    {
        "id": "common_cold",
        "text": "Common cold is a very common viral infection that affects the nose and throat. It is usually caused by viruses such as rhinoviruses and spreads easily through air droplets or contact with infected people. Symptoms often include a runny or blocked nose, sneezing, sore throat, mild cough, fatigue, and sometimes a low-grade fever.",
